comment: Iguodala (GSW) sets the screen on Paul (LAC) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Bogut (GSW) makes contact with Jordan's (LAC) arm and the contact affects his layup attempt.
Lee (GSW) enters the paint area prior to the free throw being released.
Barnes (LAC) does not give Iguodala (GSW) room to land on the jump shot as he makes knee to knee contact.
Thompson (GSW) makes incidental contact that does not affect Redick's (LAC) RSBQ.
Curry (GSW) legally contests Paul's (LAC) jumpshot. Any contact is created by Paul when he sticks his leg out.
Speights (GSW) and Jordan (LAC) briefly engage while battling for rebounding position.
Griffin (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as Speights (GSW) initiates the contact on his layup attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Lee (GSW) was upheld. Los Angeles was awarded possession and the clock was reset to 00:22.2.
Speights (GSW) makes incidental contact with Jordan (LAC) while defending.
Barnes (LAC) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Paul (LAC) muffs the inbounds pass in the frontcourt and retrieves the ball in the backcourt. A backcourt violation is correctly assessed.
Paul (LAC) trips Thompson (GSW) from behind as he defends the inbounds pass.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Paul's (LAC) foul did not meet the criteria for a clear path foul was upheld and the clock was reset to 00:09.3.
Paul (LAC) makes incidental contact with Iguodala's (GSW) arm after the made layup.
